%section
  %h1 CSS Syntax
%section
  %pre
    %code.html
      &lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css" &gt;
  %p
    A stylesheet is linked to an HTML file through the <code>&lt;link&gt;</code> tag.

%section
  %pre
    %code.css
      :preserve
        selector {
          property: value;
        }
  %p.note
    CSS rules are written following the <code>selector {property: value;}</code> structure.
    Each statement ends with a semicolon. All statements enclosed in curly braces
    affect said&nbsp;selector.

